---
description: This rule ensures that whenever website changes are requested, Cursor automatically uses the browser MCP tool to implement and verify changes on localhost:3000. The rule helps maintain quality by visually confirming that modifications appear as expected.
globs: 
alwaysApply: false
---
1. Detect website change requests in user messages
2. Open browser MCP tool pointing to localhost:3000
3. Apply requested changes to the website
4. Capture a screenshot of the modified page
5. Verify changes are properly displayed
6. Provide visual confirmation to the user
7. Ask for user approval of the changes
8. Run website tests if available